- label: --json create, --json set, --json unset, --json rm, --json link, and --json unlink mutations with multiple matching Hooks run matching Hooks sequentially after commit; when one or more earlier Hooks succeed and a later Hook fails or times out, the mutation remains committed, the successful and failing or timed-out Hook Runs persist, later matching Hooks do not run, stdout stays empty, and stderr reports the committed Hook failure or timeout
  id: 9ev
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh json_multiple_matching_hooks_stop_after_failure_or_timeout
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Plain link, --json unlink, plain single-field set, and --json single-field unset mutations whose matching Hook fails after commit still invoke the Hook with stable AGENT_STORE_EVENT, AGENT_STORE_ID, AGENT_STORE_KIND, and either link relation/target or field key/value old/new environment, leave stdout empty, and persist the Store mutation and Hook Run
